Atypical, low-energy, or low-trauma fractures of the femoral shaft (see

                               WARNINGS AND PRECAUTIONS [5.5]
                           ).

Products containing calcium and other multivalent cations (such as aluminum, magnesium, iron) are likely to interfere with absorption of ibandronate sodium tablets. Therefore, instruct patients to take ibandronate sodium tablets at least 60 minutes before any oral medications, including medications containing multivalent cations (such as antacids, supplements or vitamins). Also, patients should wait at least 60 minutes after dosing before taking any other oral medications (see 

                              DOSAGE AND ADMINISTRATION [2.3]
                           ).
